Morgan Stanley sees Bombay index at 4 , 600 in 1997 . Morgan Stanley Asia Ltd expects the Bombay Stock Exchange ' s sensitive index to rise to at least 4 , 600 points in 1997 , a senior executive said on Friday . " We see the index at 4 , 600 in the year , " Morgan Stanley Asia chairman John Wadsworth told Reuters on the margins of a business conference in the Indian capital . The Bombay bourse ' s sensitive index closed at 3 , 876 . 04 points on Thursday . The exchange was closed on Friday for a bank holiday . Asked if Morgan Stanley planned to add fresh funds to the Indian market , Wadsworth said : " We have no plans now . " - - Sabyasachi Mitra , New Delhi newsroom + 91 - 11 301 2024 
